    {
        "content": "<p>Ugh, <code>WellFoundedRelation</code> is ugly, with the bundled relation... I guess it can't be helped immediately. <code>WellFoundedLT</code> and <code>WellFoundedGT</code> seem much nicer to expose to the world.</p>",
        "id": 570463296,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1769571741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there interest in a larger project to try and upstream WellFoundedLT/WellFoundedGT? I haven't looked into it too deeply. For my purposes WellFoundedRelation would have been sufficient (it just made for a convenient way to write the Finiteness relation for the scan iterator combinator )</p>",
        "id": 570463453,
        "sender_full_name": "cmlsharp",
        "timestamp": 1769571896
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In the short term, I think upstreaming at least this makes sense</p>",
        "id": 570463503,
        "sender_full_name": "cmlsharp",
        "timestamp": 1769571931
